# No em dashes

Do not use em dashes (`—`, Unicode U+2014) anywhere in this project.

This applies to all user-facing copy, code comments, commit messages, docs, metadata, and UI strings.

## Use instead

- A comma or period for breaks in a sentence
- A colon to introduce a label or explanation
- A hyphen `-` only when joining words (e.g. `full-width`)
- Parentheses for short asides

## Examples

```tsx
// Bad
<Text>60% complete — next step with your advisor</Text>
<title>JA Group — Client Dashboard</title>

// Good
<Text>60% complete. Next step with your advisor.</Text>
<title>JA Group | Client Dashboard</title>
```

Before finishing any task, search the changed files for `—` and remove every occurrence.
